pakSettings.author: tgeorge
pakSettings.description: Custom Management Pack for Rubrik (Basic) built with MP Builder

username.label: Username
username.description: The username used to connect to the target API.

password.label: Password
password.description: The password used to connect to the target API.

configuration.label: Hostname
configuration.description: The hostname used to connect to the target API.

configuration.label: Port
configuration.description: The port used to connect to the target API.

configuration.label: Connection Timeout (s)
configuration.description: The maximum number of seconds to wait for a response from the endpoint.

configuration.label: Maximum Concurrent Requests
configuration.description: The maximum number of request that can be run simultaneously.

configuration.label: Maximum Retries
configuration.description: The maximum number of times a call to an endpoint will be retried if it fails.

configuration.label: SSL Configuration
configuration.description: The SSL mode to use when connecting to the target. Can be configured without SSL (No SSL), to use SSL but do not verify the target's certificate (No Verify), or to use SSL and verify the target's certificate (Verify).

configuration.label: Cluster Keep Alive Interval
configuration.description: The amount of time a previously collected Cluster is retained if it is not returned during collection.

configuration.label: VM Keep Alive Interval
configuration.description: The amount of time a previously collected VM is retained if it is not returned during collection.

configuration.label: Snapshot Keep Alive Interval
configuration.description: The amount of time a previously collected Snapshot is retained if it is not returned during collection.

configuration.label: Minimum Event Severity
configuration.description: The minimum severity level of events to collect.

configuration.label: Rubrik Events Keep Alive Interval
configuration.description: The amount of time a previously collected Rubrik Events is retained if it is not returned during collection.
